# =============================================================================
# CODEOWNERS — Trunk-Based Hardening
# =============================================================================
# GitHub CODEOWNERS syntax: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-customizations/about-code-owners
#
# En trunk-based, CODEOWNERS define QUIÉN puede aprobar un PR antes de mergear
# a `main`. Esto es el "human gate" complementario al "machine gate" de CI
# (lint/typecheck/test/build).
#
# Estrategia:
# - Default owner = repo owner (hammer92). Cualquier PR requiere su review.
# - Paths críticos (workflows, reglas Firebase, AI-DLC docs, arquitectura)
#   requieren review explícito del owner para hacer merge, incluso si hay
#   otros reviewers. Esto evita PRs que bypasean CI o cambian infra crítica
#   sin oversight.
#
# Cómo agregar más owners:
#   /apps/web/                    @user1 @user2
# =============================================================================

